SIMPLE: ways
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: -ways
<hw>-ways</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>A suffix formed from <xex>way</xex> by
the addition of the adverbial <xex>-s</xex> (see <er>-wards</er>). It is
often used interchangeably with <xex>wise</xex>; <as>as,
end<ex>ways</ex> or end<ex>wise</ex>; no<ex>ways</ex> or
no<ex>wise</ex>, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Way shaft</ent>⟦br⟧
